11:13 p.m.
Okay so there's a few things to consider when checking other player, and many options can be viable in a way. But most of them can have downsides as well.
  • Checking the follow up wagon. This means just mindlessly checking the player with second most votes.
  • This is most viable if the voted out player was town. Because if the player with second most votes is mafia, its possible to analyse both wagons, who on the main wagon could be a mafia trying to save his buddy who also had a lot of votes? Who was selling out?
  • This is the general default play thats always good when the vote ended up voting out a townie, because more often than not, you will likely be voting on the second highest vote duriong the following days, and resolving this issue early is pretty valuable.
  • Checking one of the loud players.
  • Knowing whether those that lead the town are also town is important, because that will let you know whether you are being deceived by them or not. It's always really bad if the Mafia has a lot of control over the conversation, and usually those that are very loud, and headstrong with their opinion, have that control.
  • Checking your personal scumread.
  • This can go either way honestly, but having personal peace with your own reads helps you a lot in determining your PoE better.
  • This is your godgiven power after all. A regular townie needs to rely on lynches and nightkills, which they can't fully control themselves. You can completely control the information you get on other players.

Shadi 2023-10-12 10:42 a.m.
After playing a while you generally start to pick up on things that a town person would generally say and vice versa Things people usually pick up on are: Agenda - Behind votes, refusal to vote, behind tunnelling/questions and reactions Tone - sometimes a good player will be able to have same tone but most people will stop sounding totally town when they’re not town at least in the long run Through relations, so let’s say you think X is scum and maybe you’re almost sure of that you don’t have a read on Y but you think X could easily be scum with Y that can help your read on Y Interaction, sometimes you can think an interaction cannot possibly be between two scums or one of the people in the interaction can’t possibly be town or scum
Ziel :D
